<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Zurn / Elkay -- Demo Execution Guide (Click-by-Click)</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --ms-blue: #0078D4;
            --ms-blue-dark: #005A9E;
            --ms-blue-light: #DEECF9;
            --accent-warm: #D83B01;
            --accent-green: #107C10;
            --accent-purple: #5C2D91;
            --accent-teal: #008575;
            --accent-red: #A4262C;
            --bg: #FAFAFA;
            --card-bg: #FFFFFF;
            --text: #323130;
            --text-light: #605E5C;
            --border: #EDEBE9;
            --shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
            --shadow-hover: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
            --radius: 12px;
        }

        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
            background: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Hero */
        .hero {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #A4262C 0%, #D83B01 50%, #FFB900 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 50px 40px 40px;
            text-align: center;
            position: relative;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .hero::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 0;
            right: 0;
            height: 4px;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #D83B01, #FFB900, #107C10, #0078D4, #5C2D91);
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: -0.5px;
            margin-bottom: 6px;
        }

        .hero .subtitle {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            opacity: 0.92;
            font-weight: 300;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .hero .meta {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 28px;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            opacity: 0.88;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .hero .meta span {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 6px;
        }

        .hero-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
            border-radius: 20px;
            padding: 4px 18px;
            font-size: 0.76rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-top: 14px;
            letter-spacing: 0.8px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        /* Container */
        .container {
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 24px;
        }

        /* Section label */
        .section-label {
            font-size: 0.72rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1.5px;
            color: var(--ms-blue);
            margin-top: 48px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        /* Pre-flight checklist */
        .preflight {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #E8F5E9 0%, #F1F8F2 100%);
            border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-green);
            border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
            padding: 24px 28px;
            margin: 24px 0;
        }

        .preflight h3 {
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--accent-green);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        .preflight ul {
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            color: #2E5A30;
            line-height: 2;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .preflight li {
            margin-bottom: 2px;
        }

        .preflight code {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
        }

        /* Collapsible sections */
        .exec-section {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow);
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-left: 5px solid var(--ms-blue);
            transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .exec-section:hover {
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-hover);
        }

        .exec-header {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 16px;
            padding: 22px 24px;
            cursor: pointer;
            user-select: none;
        }

        .exec-header:hover {
            background: rgba(0, 120, 212, 0.03);
        }

        .exec-number {
            width: 42px;
            height: 42px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: white;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .exec-header-text {
            flex: 1;
        }

        .exec-header-text h3 {
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 2px;
        }

        .exec-header-text .exec-purpose {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--text-light);
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .exec-time {
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-light);
            background: var(--bg);
            padding: 4px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            white-space: nowrap;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .exec-expand {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--text-light);
            transition: transform 0.3s;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .exec-section.open .exec-expand {
            transform: rotate(180deg);
        }

        .exec-body {
            max-height: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: max-height 0.5s ease;
        }

        .exec-section.open .exec-body {
            max-height: 20000px;
        }

        .exec-content {
            padding: 0 24px 28px 82px;
        }

        /* Step blocks */
        .step-block {
            margin: 16px 0;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            background: #F8F9FA;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--ms-blue);
        }

        .step-block.voice-step {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-red);
            background: #FFF5F5;
        }

        .step-block.chat-step {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-teal);
            background: #F0FAF9;
        }

        .step-block.copilot-step {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-purple);
            background: #F8F5FD;
        }

        .step-block.transition-step {
            border-left-color: #FFB900;
            background: #FFFCF0;
        }

        .step-label {
            font-size: 0.68rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 2px 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            color: white;
        }

        .step-label.prep {
            background: var(--accent-green);
        }

        .step-label.click {
            background: var(--ms-blue);
        }

        .step-label.say {
            background: var(--accent-warm);
        }

        .step-label.show {
            background: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        .step-label.tip {
            background: #FFB900;
            color: #5D4510;
        }

        .step-label.caution {
            background: var(--accent-red);
        }

        .step-label.copilot {
            background: var(--accent-purple);
        }

        .step-label.transition {
            background: #605E5C;
        }

        .step-label.email {
            background: #0078D4;
        }

        .step-text {
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .step-text strong {
            color: var(--text);
        }

        .step-text em {
            color: var(--accent-warm);
            font-style: normal;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .step-text .click-path {
            font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
            background: rgba(0, 120, 212, 0.1);
            color: var(--ms-blue-dark);
            padding: 2px 7px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            white-space: nowrap;
        }

        .step-text .keyboard {
            font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
            background: #323130;
            color: white;
            padding: 2px 8px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.78rem;
        }

        /* Verbatim talk track */
        .talk-track {
            background: white;
            border: 1px solid #E0E0E0;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            font-style: italic;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            line-height: 1.65;
            color: #444;
            position: relative;
        }

        .talk-track::before {
            content: '\201C';
            font-size: 3rem;
            color: var(--accent-warm);
            position: absolute;
            top: -8px;
            left: 10px;
            font-style: normal;
            opacity: 0.5;
        }

        .talk-track p {
            padding-left: 24px;
        }

        /* Sub-topic headers */
        .sub-header {
            margin: 28px 0 10px;
            font-size: 1.02rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--accent-green);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .sub-header.voice {
            color: var(--accent-red);
        }

        .sub-header.chat {
            color: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        .sub-header.leader {
            color: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        .sub-header.ai {
            color: var(--accent-purple);
        }

        .sub-header.close {
            color: var(--ms-blue-dark);
        }

        /* Callout boxes */
        .callout {
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 14px 18px;
            margin: 12px 0;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .callout.warning {
            background: #FFF4CE;
            border-left: 3px solid #FFB900;
            color: #5D4510;
        }

        .callout.critical {
            background: #FDE7E9;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-red);
            color: #5D1015;
        }

        .callout.success {
            background: #E8F5E9;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-green);
            color: #2E5A30;
        }

        .callout.info {
            background: var(--ms-blue-light);
            border-left: 3px solid var(--ms-blue);
            color: #003A6E;
        }

        .callout strong {
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        /* Data reference tables */
        .ref-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 12px 0;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
        }

        .ref-table th {
            background: #F3F2F1;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-align: left;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #D2D0CE;
            color: var(--text);
            white-space: nowrap;
        }

        .ref-table td {
            padding: 7px 12px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--text);
            vertical-align: top;
        }

        .ref-table tr:last-child td {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        .ref-table tbody tr:hover {
            background: #F9F9F9;
        }

        .ref-table code {
            font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
            font-size: 0.76rem;
            background: #F0F0F0;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .ref-table .agent-dual {
            font-style: italic;
            color: var(--text-light);
        }

        .ref-section-title {
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--accent-teal);
            margin: 20px 0 6px;
        }

        .ref-note {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--text-light);
            font-style: italic;
            margin: 6px 0 16px;
            padding-left: 12px;
            border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
        }

        .talk-points {
            margin: 12px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .talk-points li {
            font-size: 0.84rem;
            margin-bottom: 6px;
            color: var(--text);
        }

        .talk-points li em {
            color: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        /* Email scenario cards */
        .email-card {
            background: white;
            border: 1px solid #DDD;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .email-card-header {
            display: flex;
            gap: 12px;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            color: var(--text-light);
        }

        .email-card-header .email-badge {
            background: var(--ms-blue);
            color: white;
            padding: 2px 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.72rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .email-card-header .email-badge.hot {
            background: var(--accent-red);
        }

        .email-card .email-from {
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            color: var(--text-light);
        }

        .email-card .email-subject {
            font-size: 0.92rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text);
            margin: 4px 0 8px;
        }

        .email-card .email-body {
            font-size: 0.84rem;
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.55;
        }

        /* Timing bar */
        .timing-bar {
            display: flex;
            gap: 0;
            margin: 28px 0 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow: hidden;
            height: 8px;
        }

        .timing-bar .t-seg {
            height: 100%;
        }

        /* URL reference */
        .url-ref {
            font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--ms-blue);
            word-break: break-all;
        }

        /* Differentiator badge */
        .diff-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFB900, #FF8C00);
            color: white;
            font-size: 0.68rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            padding: 2px 10px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.5px;
            margin-left: 6px;
            vertical-align: middle;
        }

        /* Colors per section */
        .border-connect {
            border-left-color: var(--ms-blue);
        }

        .border-challenge {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-warm);
        }

        .border-solve {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-green);
        }

        .border-leader {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        .border-future {
            border-left-color: var(--accent-purple);
        }

        .border-close {
            border-left-color: var(--ms-blue-dark);
        }

        .bg-connect {
            background: var(--ms-blue);
        }

        .bg-challenge {
            background: var(--accent-warm);
        }

        .bg-solve {
            background: var(--accent-green);
        }

        .bg-leader {
            background: var(--accent-teal);
        }

        .bg-future {
            background: var(--accent-purple);
        }

        .bg-close {
            background: var(--ms-blue-dark);
        }

        /* Print-friendly */
        @media print {
            .hero {
                padding: 20px;
            }

            .exec-body {
                max-height: none !important;
            }

            .exec-section {
                break-inside: avoid;
            }
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .hero {
                padding: 32px 16px;
            }

            .hero h1 {
                font-size: 1.5rem;
            }

            .exec-content {
                padding-left: 24px;
            }
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 32px;
            color: var(--text-light);
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
            margin-top: 48px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="hero">
        <h1>Demo Execution Guide</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Zurn / Elkay -- Customer Service -- Click-by-Click Playbook</p>
        <div class="meta">
            <span>&#128197; March 12, 2026 -- 2 Hours</span>
            <span>&#127919; Differentiation, Not Feature Parity</span>
            <span>&#128421; Pairs with: Demo Plan Review</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-badge">Prescriptive -- Every Click, Every Word</div>
    </header>

    <div class="container">

        <!-- TIMING BAR -->
        <p class="section-label">Session Timing</p>
        <div class="timing-bar">
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 10; background: var(--ms-blue);" title="Connect ~10 min"></div>
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 5; background: var(--accent-warm);" title="Challenges ~5 min"></div>
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 80; background: var(--accent-green);" title="Day in Life ~80 min"></div>
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 15; background: var(--accent-teal);" title="Care Leader ~15 min"></div>
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 10; background: var(--accent-purple);" title="AI Agents ~10 min"></div>
            <div class="t-seg" style="flex: 5; background: var(--ms-blue-dark);" title="Close ~5 min"></div>
        </div>
        <div
            style="display:flex; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap; font-size:0.72rem; color:var(--text-light); margin-bottom:32px;">
            <span>&#9632; Connect (10m)</span>
            <span style="color:var(--accent-warm);">&#9632; Challenges (5m)</span>
            <span style="color:var(--accent-green);">&#9632; Live Demo (80m)</span>
            <span style="color:var(--accent-teal);">&#9632; Care Leader (15m)</span>
            <span style="color:var(--accent-purple);">&#9632; AI Agents (10m)</span>
            <span style="color:var(--ms-blue-dark);">&#9632; Close (5m)</span>
        </div>

        <!-- PRE-FLIGHT CHECKLIST -->
        <div class="preflight">
            <h3>&#9989; Pre-Flight Checklist (30 min before demo)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser tabs open (Edge recommended):</strong></li>
                <li>&emsp;Tab 1: D365 Customer Service Workspace -- <code>https://orgecbce8ef.crm.dynamics.com</code>
                </li>
                <li>&emsp;Tab 2: D365 Admin / Omnichannel Real-Time Analytics (open but stay on Tab 1)</li>
                <li>&emsp;Tab 3: Power Pages Portal -- <code>https://zurnelkaycustomercare.powerappsportals.com/</code>
                </li>
                <li>&emsp;Tab 4: Outlook Web -- <code>https://outlook.office.com</code> (for sending inbound emails)
                </li>
                <li><strong>In D365 Workspace verify:</strong></li>
                <li>&emsp;You see "My Active Cases" view with tier-level color pills</li>
                <li>&emsp;SLA timers are visible on at least 2 cases</li>
                <li>&emsp;Copilot panel is accessible (click Copilot icon in command bar)</li>
                <li>&emsp;Presence status is set to "Available" (green circle, bottom-left)</li>
                <li><strong>Email ready to send</strong> -- Pre-draft Scenario 1 (Ferguson flush valve) in Outlook. Do
                    NOT send yet.</li>
                <li><strong>Phone ready</strong> -- Verify Voice Channel status shows "Available" in Omnichannel panel
                </li>
                <li><strong>Portal chat tested</strong> -- Open portal Tab 3, verify chat widget appears in bottom-right
                </li>
                <li><strong>Portal persona login verified</strong> -- Sign in as <code>derek.lawson</code> or
                    <code>rachel.chen</code> using password <code>ZeDemo!2026</code>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Screen sharing active</strong> -- Share the Edge browser window (not full desktop)</li>
                <li><strong>Notifications silenced</strong> -- Focus Assist ON, Teams status DND, Outlook notifications
                    OFF</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- QUICK REFERENCE URLS -->
        <div class="callout info">
            <strong>Quick Reference URLs</strong><br>
            D365 Org: <span class="url-ref">https://orgecbce8ef.crm.dynamics.com</span><br>
            Portal: <span class="url-ref">https://zurnelkaycustomercare.powerappsportals.com/</span><br>
            Email Queue: <span class="url-ref">customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</span><br>
            Outlook: <span class="url-ref">https://outlook.office.com</span>
        </div>

        <div class="callout info">
            <strong>Portal Auth for Demo (Keep Entra Enabled)</strong><br>
            Local contact login is configured for hero personas. Use these credentials in portal:<br>
            Derek Lawson: <code>derek.lawson</code> / <code>ZeDemo!2026</code> (HD Supply, Scenario A)<br>
            Rachel Chen: <code>rachel.chen</code> / <code>ZeDemo!2026</code> (Ferguson, Scenario B)<br>
            Alternates: <code>james.morales</code>, <code>tom.harrison</code>, <code>mike.reynolds</code> (same
            password)
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- SECTION 1: CONNECT & ORIENT -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <p class="section-label">Agenda</p>

        <div class="exec-section border-connect open">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number bg-connect">1</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Connect &amp; Orient</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Build connection, set the frame, brief UI orientation</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">~10 min</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label prep">Prep</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Have Tab 1 (D365 Customer Service Workspace) visible. You should be on the
                            <strong>Home</strong> page showing the default dashboard. Copilot panel should be closed at
                            start.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Thank you all for joining. Quick intros -- I'm Bill, solution engineer focused on Power
                                Platform and Dynamics 365. Today is designed around YOUR priorities: Email Integration,
                                Workflow Automation, and Omni-Channel Case Management. But more importantly, we heard
                                from Chad -- you want to see how we're DIFFERENT, not just check boxes. So instead of
                                feature matching, we're going to put you inside the experience and let you feel the
                                difference. Let me do a quick 2-minute orientation on the workspace layout before we
                                dive in.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Point to the <strong>left navigation panel</strong> (vertical bar on left side).<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Home</span> in the left nav.<br>
                            Point to the <strong>session tabs</strong> at the top (horizontal tabs bar -- each
                            case/activity opens as a new tab).<br>
                            Click the <span class="click-path">Copilot</span> icon in the top command bar (sparkle icon,
                            top-right area) to briefly show the panel, then close it.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>This is the multisession workspace. Each case, each conversation opens as its own tab up
                                here -- like browser tabs. Your associates never lose context when switching between a
                                phone call and an email case. The left nav gives you quick access to your cases,
                                dashboards, knowledge, and queues. And the Copilot panel -- which I'll show in action
                                throughout -- lives right here, embedded in the workspace. No separate window, no
                                separate tool. Let's start working.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>Timing Check:</strong> Keep this under 10 minutes. Justin said "this is a lot of
                        verbiage for me" -- get to the live demo fast. If the room seems engaged in intros, let it flow.
                        If they're ready to go, cut to Section 3 sooner.
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- SECTION 2: THEIR WORLD TODAY -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <div class="exec-section border-challenge">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number bg-challenge">2</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Their World Today</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Validate challenges quickly -- the room wants to SEE things</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">~5 min</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label prep">Prep</span>
                        <div class="step-text">Stay on D365 Workspace. No clicks needed -- this is conversational. Keep
                            your hands OFF the screen for now. Let the room talk.</div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>We've spent time with your teams understanding the current state. Customer Care
                                Associates start their day across Salesforce, ERP screens, Outlook, Teams, and shared
                                drives. Routing involves manual triage. Information is scattered. And your tiered
                                customer model -- where an 80-20 analysis drives who gets priority attention -- requires
                                lookups to external systems that aren't always connected. Does that still ring true?
                                Anything we should add before we jump in?</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>DO NOT</strong> spend more than 5 minutes here. If anyone starts a deeper conversation,
                        gently redirect: <em>"Great point -- let me show you exactly how we address that in just a
                            moment."</em> The room wants to SEE things, not hear about problems they already know.
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block transition-step">
                        <span class="step-label transition">Transition</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Bridge to Demo:</strong> "Let me show you what it looks like when all of that comes
                            together in one place. I'm going to walk you through a Customer Care Associate's day -- from
                            the moment they log in to resolving cases across email, phone, and chat."
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- SECTION 3: DAY IN THE LIFE (MAIN DEMO) -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <div class="exec-section border-solve">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number bg-solve">3</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Day in the Life: Customer Care Associate</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Core demo -- follow an associate from login to resolution across all
                        channels</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">~80 min</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <!-- ===== 3a: CS WORKSPACE ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3a. Starting the Day: CS Workspace</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            In the left nav, click <span class="click-path">Customer Service workspace</span> (or it may
                            already be your default app).<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Cases</span> in the left nav to expand the Cases area.<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">My Active Cases</span> view (should be the default view; if
                            not, use the view selector dropdown at the top of the grid).
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>When a Customer Care Associate logs in, this is their home. No Outlook to open first, no
                                ERP to check, no Salesforce tab. Everything starts here. I can see: my assigned cases
                                with color-coded tier levels, SLA timers that tell me what's about to breach, priority
                                cases that need immediate attention, and my workload across all channels -- email,
                                phone, and chat -- in one view.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Point out these items in the grid:</strong><br>
                            1. <em>Tier Level column</em> -- color-coded pills (Tier 1 red, Tier 2 orange, Tier 3 blue,
                            Tier 4 gray)<br>
                            2. <em>Priority column</em> -- High/Normal/Low<br>
                            3. <em>SLA timers</em> -- countdown indicators (green = on track, yellow = approaching, red
                            = breached)<br>
                            4. <em>Case Origin column</em> -- icons showing Email / Phone / Web / Chat<br>
                            5. Hover over a Tier 1 case to show the SLA detail tooltip
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Unified workspace replaces 3-4 separate application windows.
                        SLA timers are live, not report-based. Tier-level pills show customer importance at a glance --
                        driven by the same ERP data that currently requires manual lookup. <span
                            class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3b: EMAIL CASE CREATION ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3b. Email Case Creation &amp; Copilot</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label prep">Prep</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>BEFORE this step:</strong> Switch to your Outlook tab (Tab 4). You should have the
                            Ferguson email pre-drafted. Now is the time to SEND it.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="email-card">
                        <div class="email-card-header">
                            <span class="email-badge">Scenario 1</span>
                            Tier 2 Distributor -- Ferguson Enterprises
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-from">From: sarah.mitchell@ferguson.com &rarr;
                            customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</div>
                        <div class="email-subject">Order Issue -- Wrong Flush Valve Models Shipped (PO #91447)</div>
                        <div class="email-body">
                            Ferguson distributor received wrong Zurn flush valve models. Ordered 24x ZN-AV-1001
                            (Aqua-Vantage) but received 24x ZN-UR-1003 (Urinal valves). Affects 3 commercial projects
                            with deadlines. Needs: (1) correct units shipped immediately, (2) return label for wrong
                            units, (3) expedited shipping.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label email">Send Email</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            In Outlook (Tab 4), click <span class="click-path">Send</span> on the pre-drafted Ferguson
                            email.<br>
                            Switch back to D365 (Tab 1).
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Let's walk through what happens when a customer emails the team. I just sent an email
                                from a distributor about a shipment issue. In the current world, someone would manually
                                create a case, copy-paste details, search for the customer record, and try to figure out
                                context from the email chain. Let's see what happens here.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>Timing:</strong> Server-side sync can take 1-2 minutes. While waiting, keep talking
                        about the current-state pain. If the case doesn't appear within 2 minutes, have a BACKUP: open a
                        pre-existing email case and say "Here's one that came in earlier through the same process."
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Once the case appears in your queue / active cases:<br>
                            Click the <strong>case title</strong> in the grid to open it as a new session tab.<br>
                            Point to: <em>Customer field</em> (auto-matched to Ferguson account), <em>Case Origin</em>
                            (Email), <em>Priority</em>, <em>Tier Level</em>.<br>
                            Scroll down to the <strong>Timeline</strong> section -- the email should be visible as the
                            first entry.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block copilot-step">
                        <span class="step-label copilot">Copilot</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Click the <span class="click-path">Copilot</span> icon (sparkle) in the top command bar to
                            open the Copilot side panel.<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Summarize case</span> (or type "Summarize this case" in the
                            prompt).<br>
                            <strong>Wait for Copilot response</strong> -- it will summarize the email content, identify
                            the customer, the problem, and suggest next actions.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>The system identified the customer, created the case, linked the email thread, populated
                                the issue details, AND applied your routing rules to get it to the right person. Zero
                                manual steps. And watch this -- I asked Copilot to summarize and it gives me the full
                                picture in seconds: what the customer is asking, the history, and suggested next
                                actions. No reading through email chains. No context assembly.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block copilot-step">
                        <span class="step-label copilot">Copilot Draft</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            In the Copilot panel, click <span class="click-path">Draft a response</span> (or type "Draft
                            a reply to this customer").<br>
                            Show the generated response -- Copilot drafts a professional reply using case context.<br>
                            <strong>Don't send it</strong> -- just show the capability and close the draft.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Auto-case creation + auto-customer matching + auto-routing vs.
                        manual triage in SF. Copilot summarization eliminates reading entire email chains. <span
                            class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3c: TIMELINE & CUSTOMER 360 ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3c. Working the Case: Timeline &amp; Customer 360</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Stay on the open case. Scroll to the <strong>Timeline</strong> section.<br>
                            Point to the email entry, any notes, any prior activities.<br>
                            Now click the <strong>customer name link</strong> (e.g., "Ferguson Enterprises") in the
                            Customer field at the top of the case form -- this opens the Account record.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            On the Account record, point out:<br>
                            1. <em>Account details</em> -- Tier classification, address, contacts<br>
                            2. <em>Related Cases</em> -- previous support history<br>
                            3. <em>Products</em> -- what they've purchased (linked via orders)<br>
                            4. <em>Timeline</em> -- all interactions across Sales AND Service<br>
                            5. <em>Entitlements</em> -- SLA terms tied to their tier
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Now look at the timeline. Every email, every phone call, every note, every internal chat
                                -- it's all here in one chronological view. And when I click into the customer account,
                                I see the same data that Sales sees. There's no integration to build -- it's the same
                                platform. Previous cases, open orders, products they own, warranty status, their tier
                                classification. This is one of the biggest differentiators: in Dynamics, Sales and
                                Service share the same data natively. There's no connector, no sync, no middleware. It's
                                one platform.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Click the <strong>browser Back button</strong> or click the <strong>case session
                                tab</strong> at the top to return to the case record.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Unified data platform -- Sales + Service + ERP visibility
                        without integration. SF requires connectors to share data between Sales Cloud and Service Cloud.
                        <span class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3d: KNOWLEDGE ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3d. Knowledge in the Flow of Work</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            On the case form, look for the <strong>Knowledge</strong> tab or the <span
                                class="click-path">Knowledge Search</span> panel on the right side (sometimes labeled
                            "Knowledge" in the productivity pane).<br>
                            If using the Copilot panel, type: <em>"Find KB articles for this case"</em><br>
                            Copilot should surface relevant articles based on the case subject/product.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Point to the suggested knowledge articles.<br>
                            Click one article title to preview it inline.<br>
                            <strong>Briefly mention</strong> the "Create article from case" capability (bottom of
                            resolved case form) -- don't demo it in depth.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>As I'm working this case, the system is already surfacing relevant knowledge articles.
                                Today, your knowledge base is primarily customer-facing -- engineering-approved articles
                                from the help center. But there's a huge opportunity here: an internal knowledge base
                                that helps Customer Care Associates resolve cases faster without having to track down
                                the one person who knows the trick. And when I resolve a case and there ISN'T an article
                                for this issue, the system prompts me to create one -- with Copilot drafting it from my
                                case notes. That goes through an approval workflow and then it's available for the next
                                associate who gets the same question.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>DO NOT</strong> go deep on KB admin, approval workflows, or the KM agent here. Keep it
                        in the flow of work. Say: <em>"We'll talk about the Knowledge Management agent in a few
                            minutes."</em>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3e: TEAMS COLLABORATION ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3e. Teams Collaboration Embedded</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            On the case form, look for the <strong>Teams</strong> icon in the command bar or the
                            productivity pane on the right side.<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Teams chat</span> or <span class="click-path">New linked
                                chat</span>.<br>
                            A new Teams chat panel opens -- notice the case title and context are auto-populated in the
                            chat header.<br>
                            Type a brief message: <em>"Checking on availability of ZN-AV-1001 -- 24 units for Ferguson
                                PO #91447"</em><br>
                            <strong>Don't actually send unless you have a recipient set up.</strong>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Here's something that closes a major gap Chad mentioned. Right now, if an associate needs
                                help, they leave Salesforce, open Teams, find the right person, manually paste case
                                context, and the whole conversation is lost to the case record. In Dynamics, I start a
                                Teams chat FROM the case -- the context comes with me automatically. When the shipping
                                coordinator replies that a part is back-ordered, I click 'Capture to Case' and it logs
                                directly into the timeline. No context switching, no lost information.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Embedded Teams with auto-capture to case record. SF has no
                        native Teams integration. Chad specifically called this out. <span
                            class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3f: NATIVE VOICE ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header voice">&#128242; 3f. Handling a Customer Call -- NATIVE VOICE</h4>

                    <div class="callout critical">
                        <strong>NON-NEGOTIABLE (Mike's Directive):</strong> "It's a non-negotiable. We need to see the
                        call center and telephony integration as part of this demo." They are open to replacing Genesis
                        entirely. GO ALL-IN HERE.
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label prep">Prep</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Before this step:</strong> Verify your Omnichannel presence shows
                            <strong>"Available"</strong> (green dot, bottom-left of workspace). Verify the Voice Channel
                            workstream is active. You'll need a second phone to call in, OR simulate the screen pop by
                            navigating to a pre-existing phone case.<br>
                            <strong>Workstream ID:</strong> <code>940cdd5e-b83e-8107-b01c-af6ed452cb25</code>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Now let's take a customer call. This is native telephony built into Dynamics -- no
                                third-party integration required. As the call comes in, the system recognizes the
                                caller, pops the customer record, and I immediately see: their account, every open case,
                                recent orders, SLA status, and their tier level. I don't have to ask 'who am I speaking
                                with?' -- I already know.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click / Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            When the call notification appears (or when you open the phone case):<br>
                            1. Click <span class="click-path">Accept</span> on the incoming call toast notification<br>
                            2. Point to the <strong>screen pop</strong> -- customer record auto-loaded on the left,
                            conversation panel on the right<br>
                            3. Point to the <strong>real-time transcript</strong> appearing on the right side as the
                            conversation progresses<br>
                            4. Point to <strong>Copilot suggestions</strong> appearing based on what's being discussed
                            -- KB articles, next best actions, product info<br>
                            5. Point to the <strong>sentiment indicator</strong> (positive/neutral/negative mood
                            reading)
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Now watch the right side of the screen. As we're talking, the real-time transcript is
                                appearing. And Copilot is listening -- it picks up on what the customer is saying and
                                starts suggesting next best actions. If the customer mentions a specific product, it
                                surfaces that product's KB articles. If they mention wanting to return something, it
                                suggests the return process. This is the Intent Agent in action -- it's guiding the
                                associate through resolution in real time.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label say">After-Call Wrap-Up</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>And here's where you save massive amounts of time. Wrap-up typically takes 5-10 minutes
                                per interaction -- associates type notes, update fields, log actions. With one click,
                                Copilot drafts the summary from the transcript, logs the actions taken, updates case
                                fields, and drafts the follow-up email. What used to take minutes now takes seconds.
                                Multiply that across every call, every day, across the entire team -- that's a
                                significant productivity gain.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block voice-step">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            After the call ends (or on the pre-existing phone case):<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Copilot</span> &rarr; <em>"Summarize this
                                conversation"</em><br>
                            Show the auto-generated call summary, auto-populated case notes, draft follow-up email.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Native telephony with real-time transcript + Copilot
                        utterance-based suggestions. Genesis Cloud doesn't integrate well with SF (Chad's pain point).
                        This replaces Genesis entirely. <span class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3g: CHAT / DIGITAL MESSAGING ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header chat">&#9654; 3g. Chat / Digital Messaging</h4>

                    <div class="step-block chat-step">
                        <span class="step-label prep">Prep</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Switch to your Portal tab (Tab 3): <span
                                class="url-ref">https://zurnelkaycustomercare.powerappsportals.com/</span><br>
                            Sign in as a known portal persona before opening chat:<br>
                            <code>derek.lawson</code> / <code>ZeDemo!2026</code> (Scenario A) OR
                            <code>rachel.chen</code> / <code>ZeDemo!2026</code> (Scenario B).<br>
                            The chat widget should be visible in the bottom-right corner. You'll use this tab to
                            initiate chat as the customer, then switch to D365 (Tab 1) to receive it as the agent.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block chat-step">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click (Scenario A -- Derek)</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            On the Portal tab (Tab 3), click the <strong>Chat widget</strong> (bottom-right bubble).<br>
                            Type: <em>"My E-Z Flush sensor isn't detecting users. We have 8 units at a hotel and they're
                                all acting up."</em><br>
                            If prompted in chat, click <strong>Login</strong> and complete sign-in with the same Derek
                            credentials.<br>
                            Then type: <em>"I've already tried batteries, sensor cleaning, and pressure checks. Can I
                                talk to someone?"</em><br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Send</span>.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block chat-step">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click (as Agent)</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Switch to D365 tab (Tab 1). You should receive an incoming chat notification.<br>
                            Click <span class="click-path">Accept</span> on the chat notification toast.<br>
                            The chat session opens in a new tab alongside your email/phone session tabs.<br>
                            Point to: HD Supply identified, Derek contact, Tier 2 context, full bot transcript, and
                            case timeline notes for firmware v2.3 humidity issue.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block chat-step">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click (Scenario B -- Rachel)</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Start a new portal session and sign in as <code>rachel.chen</code> /
                            <code>ZeDemo!2026</code>.<br>
                            In chat, type: <em>"I need a warranty claim for 50 WaterSentry Plus filters from batch
                                WS-2026-0217."</em><br>
                            Then type: <em>"I need an RMA number and I need to know where else this batch
                                shipped."</em><br>
                            Switch to D365 and accept chat. Show Ferguson Tier 1 (red), Rachel identity, and timeline
                            notes confirming the batch defect and 48-hour RMA handling.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block chat-step">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>This is the same customer service data model across channels. The customer signs into the
                                portal, the bot triages first, then escalates to a live associate with full transcript
                                and account context. For Derek, we move from self-service troubleshooting to warranty
                                replacement. For Rachel, we move from warranty policy to actual RMA and batch-impact
                                discussion. Same workspace, same routing, same Copilot assist.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Unified channel management. Chat, email, phone all in one
                        workspace with shared routing and capacity. Currently scattered across HubSpot/SF/Genesis. <span
                            class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3h: TIERED ROUTING ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3h. Tiered Routing &amp; Skills (Outcomes View)</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Go back to the email case from Section 3b (click its session tab at the top).<br>
                            Point to the <strong>Tier Level</strong> field on the case form (should show the colored
                            tier pill).<br>
                            If there's a hot-word banner visible (red/yellow bar at top of form), point to it.<br>
                            Scroll to see the <strong>Queue</strong> the case was routed to.<br>
                            If available, click <span class="click-path">Routing diagnostics</span> or point to routing
                            metadata showing why this case landed here.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Let me show you why this case landed with this specific associate. The system evaluated
                                multiple factors: the customer's tier level -- this is a Tier 1 Strategic account based
                                on your ERP classification -- so they went to the front of the line. The email subject
                                contained the word 'urgent,' which triggered our hot-word detection and escalated the
                                priority. And because this is a hydration product question, it matched an associate with
                                the right product skills. All of that happened automatically in milliseconds. No manual
                                triage, no reading the email and deciding where to route it. And if an associate is
                                already at capacity on phone calls, the system knows not to send them more work until
                                they have bandwidth.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>DO NOT</strong> open Admin Center or show rule configuration. Say: <em>"In our tech deep
                            dive session, we'll walk through exactly how these rules are set up and how they map to your
                            AIP process."</em>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Intelligent multi-factor routing (tier + keywords + skills +
                        capacity) vs. SF's queue-based or basic skills-based backlog. Unified capacity management across
                        all channels. <span class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3i: GUIDED PROCESS FLOWS ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3i. Guided Process Flows (SF "Guided Actions" Equivalent)</h4>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Custom Page Status:</strong> &#10003; Built and registered. The Order Modification
                        Wizard is live in the D365 productivity pane. Use it during the phone call demo (Section 3f).
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Benton, you asked about your guided actions -- those step-by-step wizards that walk
                                associates through complex tasks without exposing complicated forms. Let me show you our
                                equivalent. I'm going to start a warranty claim. Instead of filling out a full case form
                                with 20 fields, I click this button and get a guided experience: enter the serial
                                number, the system looks it up and pulls the product, verify the warranty status, answer
                                a couple of diagnostic questions, and it creates the claim, generates the shipping
                                label, and sends the customer a confirmation -- all in 4 clicks. This is built with
                                Power Apps, which means your team can create and modify these flows without a full
                                development cycle. And because it's all connected to Dataverse, every action is captured
                                on the case timeline.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label click">Click (if built)</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            On the case form, click the <span class="click-path">Start Warranty Claim</span> button (or
                            the guided flow tab).<br>
                            Step through: Enter serial number &rarr; Product auto-populates &rarr; Warranty status
                            confirmed &rarr; Diagnostic questions &rarr; Claim created.<br>
                            Point to the timeline entry showing the completed action.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Power Apps custom pages / canvas apps embedded in case forms --
                        equivalent to SF screen flows but with full access to the Microsoft data platform, ERP
                        integration, and extensibility. <span class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ===== 3j: PROACTIVE NOTIFICATIONS ===== -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header">&#9654; 3j. Proactive Notifications &amp; Alerts</h4>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Point to any in-app notification that may be visible (bell icon in top command bar).<br>
                            If an SLA warning toast appears, highlight it.<br>
                            Otherwise, describe the notification types verbally while pointing to the notification
                            center.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>You mentioned notification fatigue is a real concern -- associates get bombarded and
                                start ignoring everything. In Dynamics, notifications are highly configurable. You
                                decide which events matter: SLA breach approaching in 30 minutes? That's a notification.
                                A Tier 1 customer has been waiting in queue for more than 2 minutes? Alert the
                                supervisor. A hot-word case just came in? Push it to attention. But you moderate it --
                                only the high-value, actionable alerts get through. And for supervisors, the Omnichannel
                                real-time dashboard shows queue health, wait times, and associate availability without
                                needing push notifications at all.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block transition-step">
                        <span class="step-label transition">Transition to Care Leader</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Bridge:</strong> "That's the Customer Care Associate's world. Now let me switch to
                            Lisa and Michelle's perspective -- what does a care leader see?"
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
