                            2. <em>Agent availability grid</em> -- who's available, busy, away<br>
                            3. <em>Queue wait times</em> per queue<br>
                            4. <em>SLA compliance rate</em> chart (if available)<br>
                            5. <em>Conversation status breakdown</em> -- active, waiting, wrap-up
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p><strong>vs. Salesforce:</strong> In Service Cloud, you&rsquo;d need to build a custom
                                dashboard in Salesforce Reports, pull in Genesys data through an integration, and hope
                                the timestamps line up. Here the telephony data, case data, and routing data are all the
                                same system &mdash; so the numbers are always right.</p>
