                            &bull; <em>Active vs. idle time</em> breakdown<br>
                            &bull; <em>Transfer rate</em> &mdash; how often agents escalate or transfer
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Michelle, imagine your morning routine: you pull up this view, see who handled
                                the most cases yesterday, who had the longest handle times, who transferred
                                the most. That&rsquo;s your coaching conversation for the day &mdash; data-driven,
                                not anecdotal. And because WFM is integrated, you can see if someone had a long
                                handle time because they were juggling training and cases on the same shift.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>The key here is convergence. Today you have data in Salesforce, data in Genesys,
                                data in spreadsheets, and it takes days to build a picture. Here, every interaction
                                &mdash; phone, email, chat &mdash; flows through the same system, so the numbers
                                are real-time and trustworthy.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout info">
                        <strong>Tip:</strong> If the dashboard is sparse in the demo environment, say:
                        &ldquo;With 14 agents across five shifts, this view gives you instant visibility
                        that today requires pulling three separate reports.&rdquo;
                    </div>

