                    <!-- 4d: Quality Management -->
                    <h4 class="sub-header leader">&#9654; 4d. Quality Management</h4>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Setup Status:</strong> &#10003; Quality Management is fully configured and LIVE.
                        Connection references set, all 6 QEA/KM flows active, QEA + KM agents published.
                        <strong>Manufacturing Service Quality Standard</strong> criteria published with 6 sections,
                        21 AI-scored questions. Two evaluation plans published and active.
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>The last piece of the care leader&rsquo;s toolkit is Quality Management. This is
                                where supervisors can score agent interactions against evaluation criteria &mdash;
                                think of it as your QA process, built into the platform.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Navigation: Show Live Criteria -->
                    <h5 style="margin: 1.2em 0 0.6em; color: #0078d4;">Navigation: Show Live Criteria</h5>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Navigate to <strong>Customer Service admin center</strong> &rarr; <strong>Quality
                                Management</strong> (left nav) &rarr; <strong>Evaluation criteria</strong> &rarr;
                            click <strong>Manufacturing Service Quality Standard</strong>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>We&rsquo;ve built a criteria set called the Manufacturing Service Quality Standard.
                                It has six weighted sections with 21 questions &mdash; all tailored to your service
                                model.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="ref-section-title">Walk Through the Sections (scroll, don&rsquo;t read every question)</p>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Section</th>
                                <th>Weight</th>
                                <th>Qs</th>
                                <th>Key Point to Mention</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Customer Identification &amp; Account Handling</td>
                                <td>15%</td>
                                <td>3</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Did the agent verify identity and recognize the customer&rsquo;s tier?&rdquo;
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Technical Accuracy &amp; Product Knowledge</td>
                                <td>25%</td>
                                <td>4</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Heaviest weight &mdash; did the agent reference correct specs and recommend
                                    the right parts?&rdquo;</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Process Compliance &amp; Escalation Handling</td>
                                <td>20%</td>
                                <td>4</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Hot word detection &mdash; Urgent, Recall, Safety, Legal &mdash; did the
                                    agent escalate properly?&rdquo;</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Resolution Effectiveness</td>
                                <td>20%</td>
                                <td>4</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Was the issue resolved on first contact? Was documentation thorough?&rdquo;
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Communication &amp; Professionalism</td>
                                <td>10%</td>
                                <td>3</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Tone, clarity, setting expectations&rdquo;</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Tool Adoption &amp; Efficiency</td>
                                <td>10%</td>
                                <td>3</td>
                                <td>&ldquo;Did the agent use Copilot, KB, and AI tools? This rewards adoption.&rdquo;
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Every question has AI-response enabled. The Quality Management Agent reads the
                                conversation transcript and case notes, then scores each question automatically.
                                The supervisor only reviews the flagged ones.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Navigation: Show Evaluation Plans -->
                    <h5 style="margin: 1.2em 0 0.6em; color: #0078d4;">Navigation: Show Evaluation Plans</h5>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Go back to <strong>Quality Management</strong> &rarr; <strong>Evaluation plans</strong>
                            &rarr; show both plans:
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Plan</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Frequency</th>
                                <th>Scope</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Daily Case Quality Review</strong></td>
                                <td>Recurring</td>
                                <td>Daily</td>
                                <td>Cases &mdash; evaluates all resolved cases each day</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>Conversation Quality Review</strong></td>
                                <td>Trigger</td>
                                <td>On closed conversation</td>
                                <td>Conversations &mdash; evaluates every closed chat/voice interaction</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>There are two approaches here. First, manual evaluation &mdash; a supervisor picks
                                a conversation, scores it against criteria like greeting, resolution accuracy,
                                compliance language. Second &mdash; and this is where it gets powerful &mdash;
                                the Quality Management Agent. That&rsquo;s an AI agent that automatically scores
                                <em>every</em> interaction against your criteria and flags the ones that need human
                                review. So instead of randomly sampling 5% of calls, the system tells you which
                                conversations deserve attention based on sentiment, compliance keywords, or
                                resolution quality.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Lisa, think about your QA process today. How many calls does your team review per
                                week? And how do you decide which ones to review? With the QM Agent, every
                                interaction gets evaluated, and the supervisor&rsquo;s time goes to the conversations
                                that actually need coaching &mdash; not random sampling.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Navigation: Show Scored Evaluations (conditional) -->
                    <h5 style="margin: 1.2em 0 0.6em; color: #0078d4;">Navigation: Show Scored Evaluations
                        <span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: italic;">(if simulation has run)</span>
                    </h5>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label show">Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            If a simulation has been run, navigate to <strong>Quality Management</strong> &rarr;
                            <strong>Evaluation results</strong> &rarr; open a scored evaluation. Walk through:
                            <ul>
                                <li>The overall score (percentage)</li>
                                <li>Per-section scores with the weight breakdown</li>
                                <li>Click into a question to show the AI&rsquo;s selected answer and its rationale</li>
                                <li>Point out where the AI referenced specific moments from the transcript</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>The AI read the entire conversation and scored each of the 21 questions. It shows
                                its reasoning &mdash; you can see exactly why it scored this way. The supervisor
                                can agree, override, or add notes.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p><strong>vs. Salesforce:</strong> With Salesforce, quality management typically
                                requires Einstein Conversation Insights as an add-on, plus a third-party QA tool
                                for structured evaluations. Here it&rsquo;s native &mdash; same data, same
                                platform, same admin experience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block transition-step">
                        <span class="step-label transition">Transition to AI Agents</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Bridge:</strong> "You've now seen both the associate experience and the care
                            leader's view. Let me show you the AI agents that power a lot of what you've been seeing."
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- SECTION 5: AI AGENTS -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <div class="exec-section border-future">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number bg-future">5</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>AI Agents -- Outcomes Only</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Show what agents DO, not how they're configured</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">~10 min</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="callout info">
                        <strong>Benton's Guidance:</strong> "How AI's configured is probably not necessary. I think just
                        what would be their best experience." Show outcomes only.
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block copilot-step">
                        <span class="step-label copilot">Intent Agent</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>No new clicks needed</strong> -- reference back to the phone call demo (3f).<br>
                            Point back to the transcript and Copilot suggestions you showed during the voice call.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Let me show you three AI agents that come built into Customer Service. First, the Intent
                                Agent -- you've already seen this in action. During the phone call, it was listening to
                                the conversation and suggesting next steps. It uses your knowledge base, case history,
                                and product data to guide the associate to faster resolution in real time.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Second, the Case Management Agent -- this one monitors your case queue and can automate
                                follow-ups. If a case has been waiting for customer response for 48 hours, it sends a
                                nudge email automatically. If a case comes in that matches a known resolution, it can
                                suggest closing it or even handle the response without human intervention.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Third, the Knowledge Management Agent -- it monitors patterns in your cases and
                                identifies gaps. If 15 cases came in about the same bottle filler issue and there's no
                                KB article, it drafts one and routes it for review. Remember how your current KB is
                                mainly customer-facing and engineering-approved? These agents can build your internal
                                knowledge base automatically from case resolutions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Say</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>Three built-in agents with real service outcomes -- not just chatbot builders. And this
                                is just the beginning.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout success">
                        <strong>Differentiator:</strong> Three built-in agents with real service outcomes. SF charges
                        separately for many of these capabilities. <span class="diff-badge">Differentiator</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block transition-step">
                        <span class="step-label transition">Transition to Close</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            <strong>Bridge:</strong> "One last thing Mike asked us to highlight before we wrap up."
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- SECTION 6: PLATFORM & CLOSE -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <div class="exec-section border-close">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number bg-close">6</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Platform &amp; Close</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Brief extensibility mention + recap differentiators + next steps</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">~5 min</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Platform</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>One last thing Mike asked us to highlight. Everything you've seen today is the
                                out-of-the-box platform. But the entire application is built on Power Apps and Dataverse
                                -- which means your team can extend, customize, and build on top of it. Need a custom
                                warranty module? Power Apps. Need to connect to a third-party logistics system? Power
                                Automate. Need an app from a partner? AppSource has thousands, just like the AppExchange
                                you know today. And for developers like Justin, code-first options are coming that give
                                you full code-level control when you need it. The key point: this platform grows with
                                you.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="callout warning">
                        <strong>DO NOT</strong> demo AppSource or Power Apps in detail. Just state the capability and
                        move on. Per Mike: "Just mention it."
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Recap</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>To wrap up -- you asked us to show differentiation, not a checkbox exercise. Here's what
                                we showed today that's different:</p>
                            <p><strong>One.</strong> One platform for Sales and Service -- no connectors, no middleware,
                                no sync issues.</p>
                            <p><strong>Two.</strong> Native telephony with real-time transcript and AI-driven
                                suggestions -- replaces Genesis entirely.</p>
                            <p><strong>Three.</strong> Chat, email, and phone in the same workspace with unified routing
                                that considers customer tier, keywords, skills, AND associate capacity.</p>
                            <p><strong>Four.</strong> Copilot embedded everywhere -- summarizing, suggesting, drafting,
                                guiding -- reducing handle time and wrap-up from minutes to seconds.</p>
                            <p><strong>Five.</strong> Workforce and Quality Management built in -- not bolted on.</p>
                            <p><strong>Six.</strong> A platform that your team can extend with Power Apps, Power
                                Automate, and soon code-first development.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block">
                        <span class="step-label say">Next Steps</span>
                        <div class="talk-track">
                            <p>We have follow-up sessions planned: a tech deep dive for Benton, Chad, and Justin to go
                                through routing configuration, the AIP process, and guided action equivalents in detail.
                                An IT benefits session for Mike, Chad, and John on cost, contracts, and DevOps. And
                                we'll share everything you've seen today in a follow-up document. Thank you for your
                                time.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- EMERGENCY / HOT WORD SCENARIO (BONUS) -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <p class="section-label">Bonus Scenarios (Use If Time Permits or as Backup)</p>

        <div class="exec-section" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-red);">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number" style="background: var(--accent-red);">!</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Hot Word Scenario: Emergency Backflow Failure</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Shows priority escalation from hot words -- high-impact demo moment</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">Backup</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="email-card">
                        <div class="email-card-header">
                            <span class="email-badge hot">Scenario 2 -- Hot Words</span>
                            Tier 2 Distributor -- Hajoca Corporation
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-from">From: tom.garcia@hajoca.com &rarr;
                            customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</div>
                        <div class="email-subject">EMERGENCY -- Wilkins 975XL backflow preventer failed at hospital site
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-body">
                            Critical situation: Wilkins 975XL 4" backflow preventer failed at Mercy General Hospital.
                            Check valve not holding. City water authority issued 48-hour compliance notice. Hospital
                            cannot lose water service. Needs: (1) Replacement unit or repair kit shipped IMMEDIATELY,
                            (2) Technical guidance, (3) Warranty status. <strong>Hot words: EMERGENCY,
                                life-safety.</strong>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-red);">
                        <span class="step-label caution">What to Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            After sending this email and the case is created:<br>
                            1. Open the case -- note the <strong>Priority is automatically set to highest</strong>
                            (10,000)<br>
                            2. Point to the <strong>RED hot-word banner</strong> at the top of the form: "CRITICAL
                            KEYWORDS DETECTED: EMERGENCY"<br>
                            3. Point to the <strong>Queue assignment</strong> -- routed to escalation queue, not
                            standard<br>
                            4. Say: <em>"The word 'emergency' in that email automatically boosted this to maximum
                                priority and routed it to your escalation team. No human had to read it first."</em>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exec-section" style="border-left-color: #FFB900;">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number" style="background: #FFB900; color: #5D4510;">!</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Safety / Recall Scenario: Z5795 Flush Valve</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Double hot word ("recall" + "safety") -- shows maximum escalation</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">Backup</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="email-card">
                        <div class="email-card-header">
                            <span class="email-badge hot">Scenario 5 -- Recall + Safety</span>
                            Tier 1 Distributor -- HD Supply
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-from">From: david.oconnor@hdsupply.com &rarr;
                            customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</div>
                        <div class="email-subject">SAFETY concern -- Possible recall on Zurn Z5795 flush valve?</div>
                        <div class="email-body">
                            3 contractor reports of Z5795 sensor-operated flush valves activating unexpectedly and
                            continuously -- causing flooding. Affected: Hilton Garden Inn Charlotte (4 units), Duke
                            Energy HQ Charlotte (2 units), Atrium Health Clinic Concord (1 unit). Asking about active
                            recall or safety bulletin. <strong>Hot words: SAFETY, RECALL.</strong>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-red);">
                        <span class="step-label caution">What to Show</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Same pattern as Scenario 2. Point out BOTH hot words detected, double-escalation, and the
                            red banner. This is the "scary email" that leadership wants to make sure never gets buried
                            in a queue.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exec-section" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-teal);">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number" style="background: var(--accent-teal);">!</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Elkay Technical Support: Bottle Filler Troubleshooting</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Conversational troubleshooting flow -- good for KB suggestions demo</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">Backup</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="email-card">
                        <div class="email-card-header">
                            <span class="email-badge">Scenario 3</span>
                            Tier 2 Distributor -- Winsupply
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-from">From: jessica.huang@winsupply.com &rarr;
                            customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</div>
                        <div class="email-subject">ezH2O Liv bottle filler not dispensing -- model LBWD06WHK</div>
                        <div class="email-body">
                            School district reports Elkay ezH2O Liv bottle filler (LBWD06WHK) not dispensing water. Unit
                            powers on, sensor light activates, no water. Installed last week. Need troubleshooting steps
                            before school starts Monday.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-teal);">
                        <span class="step-label tip">Why Use This One</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            This is the best scenario for showing <strong>Knowledge article suggestions</strong> because
                            the product-linked KB articles should match the ezH2O product. When the case is opened,
                            Copilot/KB search should surface the bottle filler troubleshooting article. Great for
                            section 3d (Knowledge in the Flow of Work).
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exec-section" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-purple);">
            <div class="exec-header" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
                <div class="exec-number" style="background: var(--accent-purple);">!</div>
                <div class="exec-header-text">
                    <h3>Warranty / RMA Claim: Elkay Lustertone Sink</h3>
                    <div class="exec-purpose">Best for guided process flow demo (3i) -- warranty claim walkthrough</div>
                </div>
                <div class="exec-time">Backup</div>
                <div class="exec-expand">&#9660;</div>
            </div>
            <div class="exec-body">
                <div class="exec-content">

                    <div class="email-card">
                        <div class="email-card-header">
                            <span class="email-badge">Scenario 4</span>
                            Tier 3 Distributor -- Gateway Supply
                        </div>
                        <div class="email-from">From: carlos.mendez@gatewaysupply.com &rarr;
                            customerservice@D365DemoTSCE30330346.onmicrosoft.com</div>
                        <div class="email-subject">Warranty claim -- Elkay Lustertone sink rusting after 8 months</div>
                        <div class="email-body">
                            Elkay Lustertone Classic undermount sink (ELUH2816) showing rust spots after 8 months.
                            Standard residential kitchen use, no harsh chemicals. Photos attached. Need RMA process and
                            warranty replacement.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step-block" style="border-left-color: var(--accent-purple);">
                        <span class="step-label tip">Why Use This One</span>
                        <div class="step-text">
                            Best scenario for the <strong>Guided Process Flow</strong> demo (Section 3i). Walk through
                            the warranty claim wizard: enter serial, verify warranty status, initiate RMA, generate
                            shipping label. Also good for showing case status progression: Active &rarr; On Hold
                            (waiting for delivery) &rarr; Resolved.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ===================================================================== -->
        <!-- RECOVERY PLAYS -->
        <!-- ===================================================================== -->

        <p class="section-label">Recovery Plays (When Things Go Wrong)</p>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If email-to-case doesn't create within 2 min:</strong><br>
            Say: "Server-side sync runs on a schedule -- in production this is near-instant. Let me show you one that
            came in earlier." Open a pre-existing email case from the Active Cases view.
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If Voice Channel shows "Disconnected":</strong><br>
            Say: "Let me show you what this looks like from a case that was handled via phone earlier." Open a resolved
            phone case with call transcript and Copilot summary on the timeline.
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If Chat widget doesn't appear on portal:</strong><br>
            Say: "The chat experience is the same as what I just showed with email and phone -- let me walk you through
            a chat conversation from the agent side." Show a pre-existing chat transcript in D365 if available.
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If chat prompts Login unexpectedly:</strong><br>
            Use the same portal persona credentials inside the chat prompt (for example,
            <code>derek.lawson</code> / <code>ZeDemo!2026</code>). If sign-in still fails, continue from an already
            authenticated portal tab and proceed with the agent-side transcript walkthrough.
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If Copilot doesn't respond:</strong><br>
            Wait 5 seconds, then try rephrasing. If still no response, say: "Copilot is connecting -- while it loads,
            let me show you the manual path, which is what your associates do today. And THIS is what Copilot turns it
            into." Then switch to a case where Copilot has already generated a summary.
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If someone asks about admin configuration:</strong><br>
            Always redirect: "Great question. We've set that up specifically for your environment. In our tech deep dive
            session with Benton, Chad, and Justin, we'll walk through exactly how all of this is configured -- routing
            rules, queue setup, skills, the AIP process mapping. Today is about the experience."
        </div>

        <div class="callout critical">
            <strong>If someone asks about pricing/licensing:</strong><br>
            Redirect: "Dana can walk through the licensing and commercial details in our follow-up. Today let's stay
            focused on the experience and what this means for your team's day-to-day."
        </div>

    </div>

    <footer>
        Zurn / Elkay -- Demo Execution Guide (Click-by-Click) &bull; March 12, 2026 &bull; Confidential<br>
        Pairs with: Demo Plan Review &bull; Source: demo-script.md, sample-emails.md
    </footer>

    <script>
        function toggleSection(header) {
            const section = header.parentElement;
            section.classList.toggle('open');
        }
    </script>

</body>

</html>